benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/auditLogsWithHistory - Retrieve account audit logs with history by account id

covered: Valid Request: TC01 validates successful retrieval and data shape.
Empty Response: TC02 validates empty array when no logs exist.
Query Parameters & Input Validation: TC04, TC08, TC14-17, TC10 cover invalid/edge-case parameters and security.
Authorization: TC05 and TC06 verify 401 for missing/invalid tokens.
Server Error Handling: TC07 validates 500 with system error.
Performance/Load: TC09 and TC11 cover performance for large datasets and concurrency.
Data Integrity/Schema Validation: TC12 ensures mandatory fields per latest schema; TC01 covers full history fields.
gaps: Pagination: no tests for paging large result sets.
Caching Behavior: no tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control).
Explicit 404 handling guidance missing in guidelines (though TC03 tests 404).
Authorization coverage could include 403 for insufficient permissions (not tested).
Explicit security boundary tests beyond SQL injection (e.g., other attack vectors) not covered.
Rate limiting not explicitly tested beyond heavy load TC11.
recommendations: Add pagination tests (page, size, limit/offset) to validate paging behavior.
Add tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and caching validation.
Add 403-forbidden authorization scenario tests to cover all access control cases.
Clarify and align 404 handling with guidelines; ensure error messages are consistent across non-existent accounts (TC03).
Expand security tests for additional attack vectors and ensure robust input sanitization.
Introduce per-scenario SLA checks for response times under different dataset sizes (further performance testing).
